      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the wet ingredients",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan. Grease and line a 900 g loaf tin. Put the {{unsalted-butter}}, {{muscovado-dark}}, {{black-treacle}}, and {{golden-syrup}} in a saucepan over a low heat. Stir until the butter melts and the sugar dissolves. Remove from the heat and stir in the {{whole-milk}}. Leave to cool for 5 minutes, then beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine and bake, 45 to 50 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sift the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, and {{mixed-spice}} into a large bowl. Pour in the warm treacle mixture and stir until smooth and pourable. The batter will be very liquid. Pour into the tin and bake for 45 to 50 minutes. The loaf is done when a skewer inserted in the deepest part of the centre comes out clean and the surface has set firm to the touch (the top may still appear slightly damp but should not wobble). Cool in the tin for 30 minutes before turning out. Wrap in foil and leave overnight before cutting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
